data.title: Trey Drechsel
data.text:
American basketball player

Thomas Bruce "Trey" Drechsel III (born July 27, 1996) is an American professional basketball player for Benfica of the Liga Portuguesa de Basquetebol.

Early career

[edit]

Drechsel attended Cedar Park Christian High School in Bothell, Washington.

Drechsel played four seasons at Western Washington in Bellingham, Washington, from 2014 to 2018. In the 2017–18 season, he was named to the All-GNAC First Team in 2018.[1]

In 2018, Drechsel moved to Grand Canyon for his senior season.[2] He started 25 games and averaged 8.1 points and 5.8 rebounds per game.[3]

Professional career

[edit]

On July 5, 2020, Drechsel signed his first professional contract, a three-year deal with Partizan NIS of the Adriatic League.[4][5] On July 31, he was loaned to Mladost Zemun of the Basketball League of Serbia.[6] His loan ended in May 2021.[7] He parted ways with Partizan in August 2021.[8]

On August 30, 2021, Drechsel signed for Stal Ostrów Wielkopolski.[9]

On June 13, 2022, he has signed with Baskets Oldenburg of the Basketball Bundesliga.[10]
